title.narrative: FFF Sida Fair Finance Guide General Comp

description.narrative: The general support staff for the Fair Finance Guide International (FFGI) pillar of the Fair Financial Flows (FFF) program is composed of a FFGI coordinator and a FFGI digital campaigner, supported by the FFF coordinator, Finance officer, Support Officer, ICT specialist and MEAL officer. The FFGI coordinator and campaigner oversee the work realized by the 9 national FFG coalitions and they coordinate cooperation, exchange and learning amongst the coalitions. They organize all planning, monitoring and reporting required. They lead the different FFGI working groups that focus on research methodology, campaigning, case study research, evaluation processes or other specific topics such as a FFG for pension funds. They visit the coalitions in the various countries, they organize an annual meetings with all coalitions, and they reach out to allied institutions for coordination of joint actions.

participating-org.narrative: Oxfam Novib was founded in 1956 as the Netherlands Organisation for International Assistance (Novib), and joined forces with Oxfam in 1994. Oxfam Novib is member of the Oxfam International confederation. Working together in the confederation, the Oxfam affiliates can speak with one clear and compelling voice on issues of global concern: climate change, health and education for all, agriculture, trade, and conflicts and emergencies. Oxfam Novib's main office is based in The Netherlands, it supports the work of a network of local offices, the implementation of global projects, fundraising, campaigning and advocacy. Oxfam Novib’s the Hague office contributes towards this project’s implementation.
